    <text>
        <body>
            <div>
                <opener><salute>Dear Sir</salute> <dateline><placeName ref="pl0759">Stratton Street</placeName> 13 June. 1796 Monday.</dateline></opener>
                <p>I think myself very <hi rend="underline">very</hi> much oblig’d to you, for having me, and mine, so much in your recollection.</p>
                <p>
                    We dine out of town, almost every day, and to morrow we pass the day at <placeName ref="pl2577">Croydon</placeName>.. If you can make it convenient to call upon me on 
                    <del><gap unit="letters" quantity="several" reason="illegible"/></del> Thurs-day <hi rend="underline">about Eleven</hi>, I shall be quite happy to see you. nothing <hi rend="underline">particular</hi>
                    has ailed either me or my wretched <persName ref="pe0331">daughter</persName>, and the reason you did not receive the hotpress'd 
                    <bibl type="authorial"><title ref="bi0034">Whitfords</title></bibl>, was owing to a series of Blundering mistakes between <hi rend="underline"><persName ref="pe2024">White</persName>, and <persName ref="pe0387">Edwards</persName></hi>.
                    the very day I receiv'd the information of your coming to <placeName ref="pl0699">town</placeName>, I receiv’d the <bibl type="authorial"><title ref="bi0034">Books</title></bibl>
                    also, and had pack’d them for <placeName ref="pl0001">Downing</placeName>, but in consequence of your Letter I stop’d the packet, because there is some room in the box, 
                    and I thought you might have some new purchases, which you might wish to send to <placeName ref="pl0001">Downing</placeName> by the same convenience.</p>
                <p>
                    on Wednesday we go into <placeName ref="pl1388">Essex</placeName>, and on Friday morning we set out for the melancholy <placeName ref="pl1020">Isle of Wight</placeName>.</p>
                <closer>
                    <salute>I am Dear Sir, yours sincerely 
                        <lb/>and in much haste</salute>
                    <signed><persName ref="pe0313">Rich<hi rend="superscript">d</hi>: Bull</persName></signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
